<h2 id="current-assessment">Which Scenario Are We In?</h2>

<p>As of March 29, 2026, the evidence points most strongly to Scenario A (Managed Absorption). Ghana's reserves are adequate, gold exports provide a structural hedge, and the underlying economy (non-oil GDP 7.6%) has genuine momentum. The Bank of Ghana has institutional credibility from the 2023-2025 stabilisation programme.</p>

<p>The key variable is oil. If Brent stays above $110 through May, the probability shifts from A toward C. The May MPC decision will reveal how the Bank of Ghana reads the balance between growth support and inflation risk.</p>

